# Theory

## What are Components in React?

Components are the building blocks of a React application.

A component is an independent and reusable part of the user interface. Each component can contain its own structure and content.

For example, a website can be divided into different components:

- Home Component
- About Component
- Content Component

Each component can be created separately and combined to create a complete user interface.

This approach makes the code:

- Organized
- Reusable
- Easy to understand
- Easy to maintain

---

# Component-Based Structure

In React, a large application can be divided into multiple smaller components.

For example:

```text
src/
│
├── components/
│   │
│   ├── Home.jsx
│   ├── About.jsx
│   └── Content.jsx
│
├── App.jsx
└── main.jsx
